Julius Baer, Roche Holding, Swatch Group: Swiss Equity Preview

-- B y   D e r m o t   D o h e r t y
-- 
2011-03-28T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-27/julius-baer-roche-holding-swatch-group-swiss-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of
companies whose shares may have unusual price changes in Zurich.
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names. Share
prices are from the last close.  The  Swiss Market Index (SMI)  of the largest and most actively
traded companies increased 0.5 percent to 6,352.28. The broader
Swiss Performance Index also added 0.5 percent to 5775.40.  Julius Baer Group Ltd (BAER)  : The Zurich-based bank is
“always holding talks” on possible acquisitions,
SonntagsZeitung reported, citing Chief Executive Officer Boris Collardi. The shares dropped 0.4 percent to 40.24 Swiss francs.  Roche Holding AG (ROG)  : The world’s biggest maker of
cancer medicines won’t be for sale in the future and a merger
with Novartis AG would make “less sense” than it would have
five or ten years ago, SonntagsZeitung reported, citing Andre
Hoffmann, a member of the Roche family pool of shareholders. The
shares fell 0.1 percent to 130.2 francs.  Swatch Group AG (UHR)  : Chief Executive Officer Nick
Hayek said the strong franc is “really catastrophic” for the
world’s biggest maker of watches, Neue Zuercher Zeitung
reported, citing an interview. The shares fell 0.7 percent to
400.3 francs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dermot Doherty in Geneva at 
